
	<sn><md>## Global Hydrosphere{.fg-red .text-center}

The global hydrosphere consists of a ==series of reserviors== interconnected by water cycling/movement in various phases :

+++ These reserviors are :

* Oceans
* Ice sheets and glaciers
* Terrestial water(rivers,soil moisture,lakes and groundwater)
* Biosphere (water in plants and animals)
* Atmosphere
+++

Within these reserviors water is stored in any of the following `3 phases` - 
* `gas`(vapor)
* `liquid`(water) and 
* `solid`(snow)


Movement of water from one reservior to another generally occur in any of the 3 phases at varying degrees of speed.
