+++</md></sn><sn><md>## Residence Time{.fg-red}

The `average length of time` a water molecule `resides or stays` in a particular reservoir before being displaced from the reservoir `during the hydrological cycles` is called **residence time** {.bar}

Residence time of a typical water molecules in different reservoirs :

+++ see table

| Reservoir | Average residence time |
|----------|----------|
| Ocean    | `3200` years or more    |
| Atmosphere   | `10 days` or less   |
| Seasonal snow cover    | `2-6` months    |
| Rivers    | `2-6 month`   |
| Soil Moisture    | `1-2` months    |
| Glaciers    | `20-100` years    |
| Lakes    | `50-100` years   |
| Shallow groundwater    | `100-200` years    |
| Deep deepwater    | `10,000` years    |

